form_title.ms_form_title_llm_v1: U.S. Immigration and Naturalization Service, I-90 Processing Sheet

full_text: U.S. Immig tion and Naturalization S ce I-90 PROCESSING SHEET (Attach to Form 1.90 when forwarding to Service Center) APPLICATION DE CA HOYA, VICENTE Application form. Form filled out and signed. A# 10-534-184 Application fee. Check one: Correct fee attached Fcc exempt Fee receipted locally (Local receipt only required for cash) Photos. Photographs are acceptable (If not, do not accept application) Card. Check one: Valid Form I-151 seen and returned, and copy attached to application. (If Form I-151 questionable, check CIS to confirm status and attach screen print; if still questionable, refer to Investigations.) 1-551 card attached. Applicant has lost card. (Check CIS before issuing any temporary document. If CIS checked, attach screen print to application.) Applicant never received card. IDENTITY VERIFICATION Check one: Documents confirm identity Identity otherwise established (Where identity is not established at time of filing, refer applicant to Investigations for verification before accepting application.) ADIT PROCESS ADIT processing completed (signature, fingerprint, A-number on Form 1-89, Form I-89 attached) (If new I-89 based on rejection of earlier I-89, attach a copy of alien's notice to this I 89 when forwarding to the Service Center.) REMARKS: TO BE COMPLETED BY INS EMPLOYEE PRE-SCREENING APPLICATION Opts JUL 1.3.1992 IIO LOS Signature Date Title INS Office (3 letter code) FORWARD APPLICATION PACKAGE, INCLUDING PROCESSING SHEET AND I-89, NIGHTLY TO THE SERVICE CENTER
